Natatorium  : \n Description and Current Usage: \n - The natatorium is one of the finest in the college ranks and features a 25-yard, eight-lane Olympic-size pool and a separate diving tank that descends 17 feet. Other features include a first-aid and hydrotherapy room, showers and locker rooms.  \n The facility is shared by: \n - Athletic teams (Menâ€™s Swimming & Diving and Womenâ€™s Swimming & Diving) \n - Health & Applied Human Sciences Department \n - Campus Recreation Programs \n - Community lessons and meets \n - The Seahawk Natatorium has been the site of six Colonial Athletic Association championships and numerous youth swimming meets.
Almkuist-Nixon Sports Medicine Complex : \n Departments/Current Usage: \n - The 9,500 sq. ft. sports medicine complex includes a state-of-the-art sports medicine facility for the care of UNCW's 300-plus student-athletes. The facility brings together the expertise of physicians trained in primary care and orthopedic sports medicine, with coordinated physical therapy, chiropractic and acupuncture care. \n The facility houses: \n - Sports Medicine Department \n - Sports physicians office \n - Offices for trainers, coaches, and assistant coaches \n - Classrooms and conference room \n - Locker rooms \n - Hydrotherapy room
